fields.youtubeDescription: I love playing chess online but the 2D view on the screen feels very unintuitive to me - I much prefer playing with a physical chess board. Hence the Internet-Of-Things chess board was born. It connects to an online game so that the user can play chess with anyone in the world, with a real board.

fields.title: Arduino clock
fields.youtubeDescription: A clock with roots that occasionally hoots. The time it can tell without even a bell. fields.title: Leka'a's Story: Pregnant in a refugee camp
fields.youtubeTitle: Leka'a's Story: Pregnant in a refugee camp
fields.youtubeDescription: The conflict in Syria has resulted in a severe and worsening emergency. Leka'a, a Syrian refugee, told Oxfam her personal story of how she misses her family and her home. Leka'a, who is pregnant, is now one of thousands of refugees in Za'atari refugee camp, Jordan.

fields.title: Domiz camp, view from top of a water tower
fields.youtubeTitle: Domiz camp, view from top of a water tower
fields.youtubeDescription: I climbed a water tower to get this Aerial shot of Domiz refugee Camp, Kurdistan Region of norther Iraq. Around 40,000 Syrian refugees live in this camp. By Eujin Byun The number of refugees fleeing the civil war in Syria has reached 1.5 million according to the UN.
